article.headline: High Point 68, Longwood 54
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. (AP) -- Arizona Reid had 28 points and 14 rebounds to lead High Point to a 68-54 victory over Longwood on Thursday night. The Panthers (10-8) continued their stellar play at home, winning for the eighth time in nine games at the Mills Athletic Center. Reid was a big reason why against Longwood (4-19). He scored nine points as High Point closed the half with a 15-9 run to lead 32-26 at the break. High Point kept things up in the second half, stretching the lead to double digits as Longwood lost its seventh straight game. The Lancers (4-19) are in their first season of full-fledged NCAA Division I eligibility. Eugene Harris added 13 points for High Point. Kirk Williams led Longwood with 14 points and eight rebounds.
